<h2>Pass 3 — Hydrate: Full Lively Guide</h2>
<p>Below you’ll get a conversational, practical, and slightly cheeky tour through tech, tools, and how to get the most from paranormal activities as a traveler. You’ll get gear tables, costs, comparisons, safety advice, accessibility considerations, and sample itineraries so you can book or build the type of paranormal tour that suits your taste.</p>
<h3>Why tools matter (and why they don’t guarantee ghosts)</h3>
<p>You’ll hear this from a lot of guides: you don’t need gimmicks to have a spine-tingling night. But the right tech adds structure — a reason to stop and listen, a method for recording memories, and a bit of theatrical cred that helps group dynamics. Tools make your experience feel like an investigation rather than a storytelling stroll.</p>
<ul>
<li>Practical tip: Treat tech as conversation starters. A bulky camera or a spirit box gets people asking questions and being observant — that’s part of the fun.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Core tools you’ll see on tours (what they do and why guides love them)</h3>
<p>Below is a table you can use as a cheat sheet. It lists common tools, their purpose, typical cost ranges, and quick notes on using them on tours.</p>
