<h3>Safety, ethics, and accessibility — your responsibilities as a traveler</h3>
<p>You’re a guest wherever you go. Respect property, follow safety instructions, and be mindful of local customs. Here are some non-negotiables:</p>
<ul>
<li>Permission: Always ensure the operator has legal access. Never trespass.</li>
<li>Health &amp; safety: Check for policies on mobility limitations, darkness tolerance, and emergency procedures.</li>
<li>Respectful conduct: Don’t interfere with memorials or sensitive sites. Ask before touching anything.</li>
<li>Psychological warnings: Some tours involve intense themes. Ask about age and trigger warnings if you’re sensitive.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Budgeting &amp; booking basics</h3>
<p>Prices vary by location and reputation. Here’s how to get the best value:</p>
<ul>
<li>Book smaller local operators for intimate, authentic experiences.</li>
<li>Research reviews: People often report not just scares but professionalism and safety.</li>
<li>Ask what’s included: equipment usage, training, food, and morning evidence reviews add value for overnight hunts.</li>
<li>Tip guide investigators when you feel they gave extra care, but always confirm tipping norms in the country you’re in.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Sample itineraries (short &amp; long)</h3>
<p>Two quick itineraries to help plan your trip.</p>
